Decision Trees

Dataset

iris: The famous Fishers iris data set provided as a data frame with 150 cases (rows) and 5 variables (columns) named Sepal.Length, Sepal.Width, Petal.Length, Petal.Width, and Species.

CART

cart.model <- rpart(Species ~., data = iris, 
                    control = rpart.control(minbucket = 10, cp = 0))
nodes.summ <- summary(cart.model, file = tempfile())$frame
subset(nodes.summ, select = -yval2)
##            var   n  wt dev yval complexity ncompete nsurrogate
## 1 Petal.Length 150 150 100    1       0.50        3          3
## 2       <leaf>  50  50   0    1       0.00        0          0
## 3  Petal.Width 100 100  50    2       0.44        3          3
## 6       <leaf>  54  54   5    2       0.00        0          0
## 7       <leaf>  46  46   1    3       0.00        0          0
confusionMatrix(predict(cart.model, type = "class"), iris$Species)$table
##             Reference
## Prediction   setosa versicolor virginica
##   setosa         50          0         0
##   versicolor      0         49         5
##   virginica       0          1        45

C4.5

c45.model <- J48(Species ~ ., data = iris,
                 control = Weka_control(R = TRUE, M = 10))

Conditional Inference Trees

ctree.model <- ctree(Species ~ ., data = iris,
                     control = ctree_control(minbucket = 10))
confusionMatrix(predict(ctree.model), iris$Species)$table
##             Reference
## Prediction   setosa versicolor virginica
